# =============================================================================
# Code Owners
# =============================================================================
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# These users/groups are auto-requested as reviewers on PRs touching matching paths.
# Repo admins should configure branch protection to require CODEOWNERS review.

# Default: DevOps owns everything not otherwise assigned
*                                   @org/devops-team

# Core pipeline code
/modules/                           @org/devops-team @org/data-platform-leads
/scripts/                           @org/devops-team
/pipelines/                         @org/devops-team

# Infrastructure — security team must review
/infrastructure/                    @org/devops-team @org/cloud-security

# Environment configurations — environment owners must review
/config/prod.yaml                   @org/data-platform-leads @org/devops-team
/config/test.yaml                   @org/qa-leads @org/devops-team
/config/dev.yaml                    @org/devops-team

# Reports — data team owns the artifacts themselves
/reports/                           @org/data-analysts @org/data-platform-leads

# Documentation
/docs/                              @org/devops-team @org/data-platform-leads
/docs/SECURITY.md                   @org/cloud-security @org/devops-team
/docs/runbooks/                     @org/devops-team @org/data-platform-oncall

# Tests
/tests/                             @org/devops-team
